# EventPlanning Application Documentation

## 1. Introduction

The **EventPlanning** application is a comprehensive web-based platform designed to facilitate event management, including browsing events, booking tickets, managing participants, viewing venue information, and exploring event schedules. The application is developed using **Python** for the backend, with frontend components implemented in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript.

The application serves as a centralized hub for users to discover events, book tickets, manage their bookings, and for administrators to manage participants and venues efficiently.

---

## 2. Application Overview

### 2.1 Technology Stack

- **Backend:** Python
- **Frontend:** HTML, CSS, JavaScript
- **Data Storage:** Local text files (`events.txt`, `venues.txt`, `tickets.txt`, `bookings.txt`, `participants.txt`, `schedules.txt`)
- **Directory Structure:**
  ```
  /eventplanning
  ├── backend/
  │   └── app.py (handles data reading/writing and business logic)
  ├── templates/
  │   ├── dashboard.html
  │   ├── events.html
  │   ├── event-details.html
  │   ├── ticket-booking.html
  │   ├── participants.html
  │   ├── venues.html
  │   ├── schedules.html
  │   └── bookings.html
  ├── static/
  │   ├── css/
  │   └── js/
  │       └── scripts.js
  └── data/
      ├── events.txt
      ├── venues.txt
      ├── tickets.txt
      ├── bookings.txt
      ├── participants.txt
      └── schedules.txt
  ```

---

## 3. Application Features and Pages

### 3.1 Dashboard Page

- **Purpose:** Main hub displaying featured events, venues, and quick navigation buttons.
- **Key Elements:**
  - `dashboard-page` (Container)
  - `featured-events` (Div showing recommended events)
  - `browse-events-button` (Button to navigate to Events page)
  - `view-tickets-button` (Button to navigate to Bookings page)

### 3.2 Events Page

- **Purpose:** Catalog of all available events with search and filter capabilities.
- **Key Elements:**
  - `events-page` (Container)
  - `search-events-input` (Input field to search events by name or location)
  - `event-category-filter` (Dropdown to filter by event category: Conference, Music, Sports, etc.)
  - `events-grid` (Grid displaying event cards with image, title, and location)
  - `view-event-button-{event_id}` (Button on each event card to view detailed event info)

### 3.3 Event Details Page

- **Purpose:** Detailed information about a specific event.
- **Key Elements:**
  - `event-details-page` (Container)
  - `event-title` (Displays event name)
  - `event-date-time` (Displays date and time)
  - `event-location` (Displays venue/location)
  - `event-description` (Detailed description)
  - `book-ticket-button` (Button to navigate to Ticket Booking page)

### 3.4 Ticket Booking Page

- **Purpose:** Allows users to select ticket types and quantities to book tickets.
- **Key Elements:**
  - `ticket-booking-page` (Container)
  - `select-event-dropdown` (Dropdown to select event)
  - `ticket-type-dropdown` (Dropdown to select ticket type: General, Early Bird, VIP)
  - `ticket-quantity-input` (Input to enter number of tickets)
  - `book-now-button` (Button to confirm booking)
  - `booking-confirmation` (Div to display booking confirmation message)

### 3.5 Participants Management Page

- **Purpose:** Manage event participants and their statuses.
- **Key Elements:**
  - `participants-page` (Container)
  - `participants-table` (Table listing participants with name, event, status)
  - `add-participant-button` (Button to add new participant)
  - `search-participants-input` (Input to search participants by name or email)
  - `participant-status-filter` (Dropdown to filter by status: Registered, Confirmed, Attended)

### 3.6 Venues Page

- **Purpose:** Display available venues with detailed information.
- **Key Elements:**
  - `venues-page` (Container)
  - `venues-grid` (Grid displaying venue cards with capacity and amenities)
  - `search-venues-input` (Input to search venues by name or location)
  - `venue-capacity-filter` (Dropdown to filter by capacity: Small, Medium, Large)
  - `view-venue-details-{venue_id}` (Button to view detailed venue info)

### 3.7 Schedules Page

- **Purpose:** Display event schedules and sessions.
- **Key Elements:**
  - `schedules-page` (Container)
  - `schedules-timeline` (Div showing timeline of sessions)
  - `schedule-filter-date` (Date input to filter schedules)
  - `schedule-filter-venue` (Dropdown to filter by venue)
  - `export-schedule-button` (Button to export schedule data)

### 3.8 Bookings Summary Page

- **Purpose:** Display user bookings with status and details.
- **Key Elements:**
  - `bookings-page` (Container)
  - `bookings-table` (Table listing bookings with event, date, ticket type, status)
  - `booking-search-input` (Input to search bookings by name or booking ID)
  - `cancel-booking-button-{booking_id}` (Button to cancel booking)
  - `back-to-dashboard-button` (Button to return to Dashboard)

---

## 4. Data Files and Formats

### 4.1 Events Data (`events.txt`)

- **Format:**  
  `event_id|event_name|category|date|time|location|description`

- **Example:**  
  ```
  1|Tech Conference|Conference|2025-03-15|09:00|San Francisco|Annual technology conference discussing latest trends.
  2|Summer Music Festival|Music|2025-06-20|20:00|New York|Three-day music festival featuring international artists.
  3|Marathon Championship|Sports|2025-04-10|07:00|Downtown Loop, Chicago|Annual marathon event for all skill levels.
  ```

### 4.2 Venues Data (`venues.txt`)

- **Format:**  
  `venue_id|name|location|capacity|amenities`

- **Example:**  
  ```
  1|Convention Center|San Francisco, CA|5000|WiFi, Food, Parking
  2|Central Park|New York, NY|10000|Outdoor Space, Food Stalls
  3|Downtown Loop|Chicago, IL|3000|Medical, Security
  ```

### 4.3 Tickets Data (`tickets.txt`)

- **Format:**  
  `ticket_id|event_id|ticket_type|price|available_count|sold_count`

- **Example:**  
  ```
  1|1|General|49.99|500|150
  2|1|Early Bird|39.99|1000|750
  3|2|VIP|99.99|100|50
  ```

### 4.4 Bookings Data (`bookings.txt`)

- **Format:**  
  `booking_id|name|event_id|date|ticket_quantity|ticket_type|total_price|status`

- **Example:**  
  ```
  1|Johnson|1|2025-02-01|2|General|99.98|Confirmed
  2|Bob|2|2025-02-05|4|Early Bird|159.96|Confirmed
  3|Carol Davis|1|2025-02-10|1|VIP|99.99|Pending
  ```

### 4.5 Participants Data (`participants.txt`)

- **Format:**  
  `participant_id|event_id|name|email|booking_id|status|registration_date`

- **Example:**  
  ```
  1|1|Michael|michael@example.com|1|Confirmed|2025-01-15
  2|2|Bob|bob@example.com|2|Registered|2025-01-20
  3|1|Alice|alice@example.com|3|Attended|2025-02-10
  ```

### 4.6 Schedules Data (`schedules.txt`)

- **Format:**  
  `schedule_id|event_id|session_title|session_time|duration_minutes|speaker|venue_id`

- **Example:**  
  ```
  1|1|Opening Keynote|09:00|60|John Smith|1
  2|1|Panel Discussion|10:30|90|Various Speakers|1
  3|2|Main Concert|20:00|120|Headliner Band|2
  ```

---

## 5. Development Guidelines

### 5.1 Backend

- Implemented in Python.
- Responsible for reading and writing data files.
- Handles business logic such as event browsing, ticket booking, participant management, venue info, and schedule management.
- Serves data to frontend templates.

### 5.2 Frontend

- HTML templates correspond to each page described above.
- JavaScript (`static/js/scripts.js`) handles interactivity such as filtering, searching, and dynamic content updates.
- CSS styles the application for a user-friendly interface.
- The root URL `/` should serve the Dashboard page.

### 5.3 Workflow and Task Management

- Tasks should be decomposed into manageable subtasks with clear responsibilities.
- Frontend and backend development should be coordinated to ensure seamless integration.
- Frontend code must be complete and correspond to backend data structures.
- Use consistent naming conventions for HTML element IDs and classes as specified.
- Ensure the application is accessible and responsive.

---

## 6. Summary

The **EventPlanning** application is a Python-based web platform designed to manage events, tickets, participants, venues, schedules, and bookings. It uses local data files for storage and provides a rich user interface with multiple pages for different functionalities. The application architecture separates backend logic and frontend presentation, ensuring maintainability and scalability.

This documentation serves as a guide for developers and stakeholders to understand the application's structure, data formats, and development requirements.
